# Scenario: Link header is present, well-known URL also resolves; agent MUST use the header.
# Expected outcome: agent fetches https://example.com/agent-catalog.json (from the header), NOT /.well-known/agent-catalog.json.

### Initial request to any URL on the origin
GET https://example.com/some/page HTTP/1.1
Accept: text/html

### Response (the publisher includes a Link header)
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/html
Link: <https://example.com/agent-catalog.json>; rel="agent-catalog"
Cache-Control: max-age=300

<html>...</html>

### Agent next request (using the URL from the Link header)
GET https://example.com/agent-catalog.json HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json
